<h1>Problem 361 - 2020 USA TST, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Two circles \(\Gamma_1\) and \(\Gamma_2\) have common external tangents \(\ell_1\) and \(\ell_2\) meeting at \(T\). Suppose \(\ell_1\) touches \(\Gamma_1\) at \(A\) and \(\ell_2\) touches \(\Gamma_2\) at \(B\). A circle \(\Omega\) through \(A\) and \(B\) intersects \(\Gamma_1\) again at \(C\) and \(\Gamma_2\) again at \(D\), such that quadrilateral \(ABCD\) is convex.</p>
<p>Suppose lines \(AC\) and \(BD\) meet at point \(X\), while lines \(AD\) and \(BC\) meet at point \(Y\). Show that \(T\), \(X\), \(Y\) are collinear.</p>
